<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
Native to the Palaearctic region. Widespread in Central Europe (
<bibRefCitation author="Alonso-Zarazaga, MA" journalOrPublisher="A., Zaragoza" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" publicationUrl="http://graellsia.revistas.csic.es/index.php/graellsia/article/view/537/636" refId="B2" refString="Alonso-Zarazaga, MA, Barrios, H, Borovec, R, Bouchard, P, Caldara, R, Colonnelli, E, Gueltekin, L, Hlavac, P, Korotyaev, B, Lyal, CHC, Machado, A, Meregalli, M, Pierotti, H, Ren, L, Sanchez-Ruiz, M, Sforzi, A, Silfverberg, H, Skuhrovec, J, Tryzna, M, Velazquez, de Castro AJ, Yunakov, NN, 2017. Cooperative Catalogue of Palaearctic ColeopteraCurculionoidea. Monografias electronicas SEA 8. Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa S.E. A., Zaragoza" title="Cooperative Catalogue of Palaearctic ColeopteraCurculionoidea. Monografias electronicas SEA 8. Sociedad Entomologica Aragonesa S. E." url="http://graellsia.revistas.csic.es/index.php/graellsia/article/view/537/636" year="2017">Alonso-Zarazaga et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Adventive in the Nearctic region (Ontario, Canada).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="canadian records">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Canadian records.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Ontario: Rouge National Urban Park, 24-Jun-2017 to 25-Jun-2017 (1 ex, CBG).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="diagnostic information">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Diagnostic information</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
(based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Rheinheimer, J" journalOrPublisher="Landesanstalt fuer Umwelt, Messungen und Naturschutz Baden-Wuerttemberg (LUBW), Ubstatdt-Weiher" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B176" refString="Rheinheimer, J, Hassler, M, 2013. Die Ruesselkaefer Baden-Wuerttembergs (2nd ed.). Landesanstalt fuer Umwelt, Messungen und Naturschutz Baden-Wuerttemberg (LUBW), Ubstatdt-Weiher" title="Die Ruesselkaefer Baden-Wuerttembergs (2 nd ed.)." year="2013">Rheinheimer and Hassler 2013</bibRefCitation>
). Body length: 2.7-3.4 mm. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 46–48" captionStartId="F27" captionText="Figures 46 - 48. 46 Ceutorhynchus inaffectatus Gyllenhal 46 A habitus, L. Borowiec 46 B aedeagus 47 Ceutorhynchus mutabilis Dietz, habitus 48 Exomias trichopterus (Gautier des Cottes) 48 A male habitus, L. Borowiec 48 B female habitus, L. Borowiec. Scale bars: 1.0 mm (46 A; 47; 48), 0.5 mm (46 B)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.894.37862.figures46-48" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362163" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.894.37862.figures46-48">Fig. 48A, B</figureCitation>
. Body brown to black, covered with fine semi-erect to erect setae, legs pale yellow to red-brown. Rostrum with shallow longitudinal depression dorsally. Globose elytra with humeral angles obsolete. Elytra lacking row of long setae near suture on posterior half.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="bionomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Bionomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
This common European species is polyphagous on herbaceous plants (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10043-011-0031-1" author="Balalaikins, M" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Lithuanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="253 - 262" refId="B13" refString="Balalaikins, M, 2011. On Latvian Entiminae (Coleoptera: Curculionidae): 2. Tribes Trachyphloeini Lacordaire, 1863 and Sciaphilini Sharp, 1891. Acta Zoologica Lithuanica 21: 253 - 262" title="On Latvian Entiminae (Coleoptera: Curculionidae): 2. Tribes Trachyphloeini Lacordaire, 1863 and Sciaphilini Sharp, 1891." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10043-011-0031-1" volume="21" year="2011">Balalaikins 2011</bibRefCitation>
) and could become a new pest of berry crops in Canada (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1134/S0013873817030149" author="Kolov, SV" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Review" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="404 - 405" refId="B117" refString="Kolov, SV, Korotyaev, BA, 2017. On establishing of two weevils (Coleoptera, Curculionidae: Entiminae) damaging fruit and berry crops in Southeastern Kazakhstan. Entomological Review 97: 404 - 405" title="On establishing of two weevils (Coleoptera, Curculionidae: Entiminae) damaging fruit and berry crops in Southeastern Kazakhstan." url="https://doi.org/10.1134/S0013873817030149" volume="97" year="2017">Kolov and Korotyaev 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Exomias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Exomias trichopterus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trichopterus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Exomias trichopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very similar in appearance to 
<taxonomicName genus="E." lsidName="E. pellucidus" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="subspecies" species="pellucidus" subspecies="pellucidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">E. pellucidus pellucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Boheman, 1834), another adventive Palaearctic species which is common and widespread in North America. Both species were previously placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacquelin du Val, 1854. The former" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Barypeithes" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" infraspecific-rank="subgenus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Barypeithes (Exomias)" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Exomias">Barypeithes Jacquelin du Val, 1854. The former subgenus Exomias</taxonomicName>
was elevated to the generic level by 
<bibRefCitation author="Borovec, R" editor="Loebl, I" journalOrPublisher="The Nature Publishing Company, Indianapolis" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B21" refString="Borovec, R, Loebl, I, Smetana, A, 2013. Sciaphilini. In: LoeblISmetanaA (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol.8). Brill, Leiden, 83, 377-386." title="Sciaphilini. In: LoeblISmetanaA (Eds) Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera (Vol. 8). Brill, Leiden, 83, 377 - 386." year="2013">Borovec (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Exomias" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Exomias pellucidus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subspecies" species="pellucidus" subspecies="pellucidus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Exomias pellucidus pellucidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be diagnosed primarily by the noticeably denser setae on their elytra, especially near the apex where an additional row of long setae is present along the elytral suture.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
